Matthew J





 

 
Matthew J. Espe 


Chairman and Chief Executive Officer
IKON 
Office Solutions


 
Matthew J. Espe joined 
IKON Office Solutions in August 2002 as president and chief executive officer, 
and was elected to the additional position of chairman of the Board of Directors 
in February 2003. Espe brings more than 20 years experience in distribution, 
sales and marketing to the position with a proven track record for building and 
leading businesses on a global scale. 
 
Since 
joining IKON, Espe has developed and executed a comprehensive strategy of 
operational excellence and market leadership, designed to establish IKON as the 
world�s largest independent distribution channel for document management systems 
and services.
 
Working 
with the IKON senior team, Espe has implemented various initiatives with key 
suppliers to enhance IKON�s product portfolio, and has invested in channel 
expansion initiatives and targeted growth programs for North American metro 
markets and major cities across Western Europe. With a focus on operational 
excellence, Espe has strengthened efficiencies and implemented programs to 
leverage IKON�s infrastructure.  In addition, under Espe�s leadership, the 
company launched IKON Enterprise Services, a world-class services organization 
to complement IKON�s best-in-class hardware portfolio and grow the company�s 
document management services offerings.

Prior to joining IKON Office Solutions, Espe served in various positions at 
General Electric Corporation, including president and CEO of GE Lighting, until 
2002. After positions of increasing responsibility in sales and marketing 
management, he was appointed a company officer of GE in 1998 and appointed 
president, GE Plastics Asia. In 1999 he was appointed president, GE Plastics 
Europe. Espe returned to the U.S. in 2000 and was named president and CEO of GE 
Lighting and senior vice president of General Electric.

In addition to his duties at IKON, Espe serves on various boards and outside 
advisory councils, including the Board of Directors for Unisys Corporation, the 
SIFE Board of Directors and the Advisory Board of the University of Idaho. Espe 
is an active volunteer with the United Way, and currently serves on the board 
for the United Way of Southeastern Pennsylvania and is the Vice Chair for the 
2006 United Way Campaign for Southeastern Pennsylvania. 
 
Espe 
earned his bachelor�s degree in Marketing from the University of Idaho and his 
M.B.A. from Whittier College.

















